A local government collation officer, Jafaru Abass Ibrahim also testified that he was surprised to see people being “transported from one polling unit to another.” He said he received reports from polling unit agents and went to confirm that many people were voting without card readers and accreditation in the 322 polling units of the area and he helped to chase some of them away. But under cross examination by defence lawyers: Yunus Ustaz Usman (INEC); Yusuf Ali (President Buhari) and Adeniyi Akintola, he admitted that nobody was arrested or prosecuted by security agencies. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE FCT polls: Voters throng markets, boycott election in Abuja satellite towns Lagos: INEC ready for Saturday’s supplementary poll Mararaba elders demand  50 more polling units Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin